text:
Colerain ranked No. 22 in MaxPreps Xcellent 25 
Updated: Mon, Oct 26 2015, 01:41 PM 
CINCINNATI (WKRC) -- The Colerain High School football team is ranked No. 22 in this week's MaxPreps Xcellent 25 national rankings. 
The Cardinals (8-1) beat Hamilton this past Thursday 42-8 and will close the regular-season at Oak Hills this Friday before beginning Division I playoff action the following week. 
Colerain's only loss this season came in the third game of the season against LaSalle, 39-36. LaSalle was ranked in the Xcellent 25 for several weeks this season. 
Colerain has outscored its six Greater Miami Conference opponents 222-56.
